fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.architectures

Class Architecture

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.architectures.Architecture
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ArchitectureI, java.io.Serializable

    public class Architecture
extends java.lang.Object
implements ArchitectureI
    The class Architecture describes a DEVS simulation architecture with a set of the atomic model descriptors, a set of the coupled model descriptors and the URI of the root model.

      • isComplete

        public boolean isComplete()
        Description copied from interface: ArchitectureI
        return true if the model architecture can be interpreted as complete i.e., all models mentioned as submodels, sources or sinks of events have descriptors defined in this model architecture.

        Detecting that an architecture is complete is complex. A possibility would be to have a specific method to be called to inform that the architecture is complete, but in practice, if the architecture is constructed by gathering model descriptions from several parallel or distributed processes, it would be extremely difficult (and probably repetitive in terms of coding) to check that all models have been added to the architecture. Hence, the basic idea of the test is to check that the root model has been defined and that no models mention the URI of another model that has not been added yet.

        Contract

         pre    true            // no precondition.
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Specified by:
        isComplete in interface ArchitectureI
        Returns:
        true if the model architecture can be interpreted as complete.
        See Also:
        ArchitectureI.isComplete()
